## Required Fields

### YAML Frontmatter (Required)

**ALL guide files MUST include this YAML frontmatter:**

```yaml
---
title: Guide Title                    # REQUIRED - Display title
description: Guide description        # OPTIONAL - Short description for cards/list
category: Category Name               # REQUIRED - For grouping guides
tags: [tag1, tag2]                     # OPTIONAL - Array of tags for filtering
author: GitHub Username                # OPTIONAL - Use GitHub username (preferred over generic team names)
date: YYYY-MM-DD                      # REQUIRED - Publication date (ISO format)
---
```

**Field Requirements:**
- `title` - **REQUIRED** - The guide title (used in navigation and display)
- `description` - **OPTIONAL** - Short description shown in guide cards/list
- `category` - **REQUIRED** - Category for grouping (e.g., "Getting Started", "Advanced", "API")
- `tags` - **OPTIONAL** - Array of tags for search/filtering (e.g., `[basics, setup, onboarding]`)
- `author` - **OPTIONAL** - Author name (use GitHub username when available, to show proper authorship attribution)
- `date` - **REQUIRED** - Publication date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format (ISO date)

### Markdown Creation Fields (Required)

**ALL guide files MUST include these fields after the frontmatter:**

```markdown
# Guide Title

**Creation Date:** [Full Month Name DD, YYYY]
**Updated Date:** [Full Month Name DD, YYYY]

---
```

**Field Requirements:**
- `**Creation Date:**` - **REQUIRED** - Full date when guide was created (Month DD, YYYY format)
- `**Updated Date:**` - **REQUIRED** - Full date when guide was last updated (Month DD, YYYY format)
- ~~`**Github username:**`~~ - **REMOVED** - No longer needed. Use `author` field in frontmatter instead (which displays above the guide)

**Note:** The `# Guide Title` should match the `title` field in the frontmatter.

